An official of the NYS has been charged with abuse of office for allegedly procuring the payment of Sh4,476,000 without the approval of the tender committee.Deputy director general Clare Lwali was accused of using her office at the NYS headquarters to improperly order the payment of the amount to M/s Naro Moru River Lodge.This was for the provision of accommodation and conference facilities on September 26, 2015.Lwali denied the charge on Tuesday before senior principal magistrate Lawrence Mugambi of the Milimani Anti-Corruption Court.She was released on a bond of Sh1 million or Sh600,000 cash bail.